271
00:18:23.291 --> 00:18:24.583
Yeah.

272
00:18:44.541 --> 00:18:48.375
Mpume. my legs were constantly in the air.

273
00:18:48.458 --> 00:18:51.000
I left Soweto a sweet little girl.

274
00:18:51.083 --> 00:18:53.833
You know?
And I came back a fully grown woman.

275
00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.500
Uh. hold on. does he have a big belly…

276
00:18:56.583 --> 00:18:59.083
-…that hides his machine?
-No. no. no. His machine?

277
00:18:59.166 --> 00:19:00.541
His machine really works.

278
00:19:00.625 --> 00:19:03.000
It works in the morning.
during the day. and at night.

279
00:19:03.083 --> 00:19:05.958
Morning. during the day.
and night. It works--

280
00:19:06.041 --> 00:19:09.250
So your phone does work?
You've been ignoring me all weekend.

281
00:19:09.333 --> 00:19:11.000
-Xolani. give me my phone.
-Just wait a minute.

282
00:19:11.083 --> 00:19:13.208
-I wasn't ignoring you.
-Piss off. Lindani.

283
00:19:13.750 --> 00:19:15.500
-Give me. my--
-Actually. you're full of shit.

284
00:19:15.583 --> 00:19:17.125
You think I'm a fool.

285
00:19:17.208 --> 00:19:20.208
I'm not. I was with Mpume
the whole weekend doing an assignment.

286
00:19:20.291 --> 00:19:22.583
Fuck that assignment shit.
Let's see who you've been talking to.

287
00:19:22.666 --> 00:19:25.041
-Xolani. my phone.
-Just wait. Give me a minute.

288
00:19:26.000 --> 00:19:27.208
Xolani!

289
00:19:32.375 --> 00:19:33.541
Xolani.

290
00:19:36.291 --> 00:19:38.083
I have the right thing for you.

291
00:19:38.166 --> 00:19:40.500
-Let me take it out for you.
-Wow.

292
00:19:40.583 --> 00:19:42.041
Let me plug you.

293
00:19:42.125 --> 00:19:43.833
You carry panties around in your bag?

294
00:19:43.916 --> 00:19:47.125
When you go to Bonginkosi wearing this…

295
00:19:48.250 --> 00:19:49.916
What the fuck is this?

296
00:19:50.000 --> 00:19:52.000
And something you ladies should know

297
00:19:52.083 --> 00:19:54.875
is if you don't put out. he won't stay.

298
00:19:56.416 --> 00:19:58.916
Bongs would never cheat on me.

299
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:00.416
He's nothing like my dad.

300
00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:02.708
Girl. you're absolutely right.

301
00:20:02.791 --> 00:20:04.833
Your father is something else.

302
00:20:12.291 --> 00:20:14.333
Oh. no! Lindani.

303
00:20:17.791 --> 00:20:19.208
Is it mine?

304
00:20:19.916 --> 00:20:22.541
How can you even ask me
something like that. Xolan?

305
00:20:23.208 --> 00:20:25.875
You think I haven't noticed
your shady behavior of late?

306
00:20:27.333 --> 00:20:29.583
You're always at Mpume's every weekend.

307
00:20:31.041 --> 00:20:33.208
Now I'm trying to process everything.

308
00:20:39.250 --> 00:20:44.375
Look. you know me better than anyone.
You know what type of man I am.

309
00:20:44.958 --> 00:20:46.083
I know.

310
00:20:46.791 --> 00:20:49.041
If I have to be responsible
for this child. I will.

311
00:20:50.375 --> 00:20:52.625
What I need you to do is
look me in the eyes

312
00:20:53.500 --> 00:20:56.125
and swear on your mother's life
that it's mine.

313
00:20:57.666 --> 00:20:58.791
Please.

314
00:21:00.708 --> 00:21:02.791
Who else could this child belong to?

315
00:21:13.583 --> 00:21:15.708
I hope those 11-course meals
were worth it.

316
00:21:16.333 --> 00:21:17.916
-Xolani.
-Mm-mmm.

317
00:21:27.166 --> 00:21:30.416
Don't cry. baby girl. Don't cry.

318
00:21:31.416 --> 00:21:36.250
You know what they say.
a child-- a child is a blessing.

319
00:21:37.416 --> 00:21:41.333
No matter how messy the situation is.

320
00:21:42.375 --> 00:21:45.583
Uh-uh. Uh-uh. Uh-uh. Uh-uh.

321
00:21:47.791 --> 00:21:49.625
I don't want to see you crying again.

322
00:21:50.875 --> 00:21:52.958
We'll work it out.

323
00:21:55.666 --> 00:21:57.166
How will we work it out?

324
00:21:58.166 --> 00:21:59.291
Look.

325
00:22:01.166 --> 00:22:04.083
I'll get you a nanny
to help you with the baby.

326
00:22:04.666 --> 00:22:06.958
So that you can carry on with school.

327
00:22:07.583 --> 00:22:09.166
Don't worry. you'll be fine.

328
00:22:11.000 --> 00:22:12.166
This is a blessing.

329
00:22:27.375 --> 00:22:29.250
You brought me to a club?

330
00:22:33.125 --> 00:22:35.666
I thought I'd surprise you…

331
00:22:35.750 --> 00:22:38.250
-Wow.
-…'cause you always do nice things for me.

332
00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:43.708
You. you're crazy.

333
00:22:43.791 --> 00:22:46.791
-Me? I'm crazy?
-Yes.

334
00:22:48.375 --> 00:22:49.833
What do you mean I'm crazy?

335
00:22:51.250 --> 00:22:52.250
Hmm?

336
00:22:52.333 --> 00:22:53.875
Can't you tell?

337
00:23:01.583 --> 00:23:02.583
No.

338
00:24:07.416 --> 00:24:09.875
You know she's a sweet girl.

339
00:24:10.541 --> 00:24:11.625
Yes.

340
00:24:13.708 --> 00:24:15.458
Don't be so scared.

341
00:24:18.166 --> 00:24:20.750
You're such a coward. my boy.

342
00:24:20.833 --> 00:24:21.916
Huh?

343
00:24:22.750 --> 00:24:24.250
And you're giving up on that?

344
00:24:28.458 --> 00:24:30.791
She-- She has a boyfriend.

345
00:24:30.875 --> 00:24:34.458
Listen here.
What's the old saying. brother?

346
00:24:34.541 --> 00:24:36.916
You find a partner from someone else.

347
00:24:37.000 --> 00:24:39.041
-Exactly.
-Take her from him.

348
00:24:39.125 --> 00:24:40.500
Take her from him.
